    <text xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Db_Cave65">
        <body>
            <div type="cave" xml:lang="zh">
                <head type="cave">
                    <hi rend="bold">65</hi>號窟</head>
                <div>
                    <head>描述</head>
                    <div>
                        <head>概述</head>
                        <p>該標準方形窟牆壁平直，但未經過打磨，亦未刊刻經文（<ptr target="WFY_65_2007_w65-0.jpg"/>）。其重要性在於窟内一處宋代干支紀年題記，提及（前）院主惠文住持，可對應北宋景德四年正月十七日（1007年2月7日）或北宋治平四年正月十七日（1067年2月3日）。銘文及有關其年代的討論，見<ptr type="infra" target="colophon_Huiwen_zh"/>。<!--題記爲：講經論沙門惠文發心，畫廣齊靈濟護法土地三身同一堂，永為供養，意乞闔院僧童，講道修行。以皇宋丁未歲正月十七日了謹記。-->
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>位置</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>位於南崖，<foreign xml:lang="en">D</foreign>區。高於現今步道約280厘米。位於<hi rend="bold">64</hi>號立佛以東，<hi rend="bold">70</hi>號窟以西，<hi rend="bold">68</hi>號龕之下。</item>
                            <item>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">f</foreign>壁方向：352°</item>
                        </list>
                        <p/>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>形制</head><!--<list>
                            <item/>
                        </list>-->
                        <p>標準敞口方形窟。除<foreign xml:lang="en">e</foreign>壁三處宋代方形打磨方塊外，三壁均未經過細磨。方形打磨方塊上，曾繪地方神祇像（<ptr target="WFY_65e_DSC8669_2015.jpg"/>）。<note>有關所繪神祇像的討論，見本卷<ptr type="infra" target="colophon_Huiwen_zh"/>。</note>居中打磨方塊下距窟内地面81厘米，打磨方塊尺寸爲76×65－66厘米。西側打磨方塊下距窟内地面78厘米，尺寸爲69×65厘米。東側打磨方塊下距窟内地面73厘米，尺寸爲49×55厘米。居中打磨方塊正上方突起的小塊方形區，尺寸爲29×17－18.5厘米，刊刻上述宋代題記（<ptr target="WFY_65e_colophon_DSC8697.jpg"/>）。
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>尺寸</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">d</foreign>壁：前部高236厘米，後部高224厘米，寬190厘米。</item>
                            <item>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">e</foreign>壁：中部高240厘米，寬216厘米。</item>
                            <item>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">f</foreign>壁：前部高227厘米，後部高230厘米，寬204厘米。</item>
                            <item>窟口：寬192厘米。</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Db_Cave65_discussion_zh">
                    <head>討論</head>
                    <bibl>
                            鄧之金<ref type="biblio" target="Dengzhijin1993">第37頁；第40頁，註釋3</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>鄧之金迻録了惠文題記，提供題記所在打磨方塊的測量數據。在註釋中，他提到惠文曾任卧佛院住持，并將題記“丁未”年比定爲北宋治平四年（1067）。</p>
                            <p/>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                            秦臻、張雪芬、雷玉華<ref type="biblio" target="Qin_Zhang_Lei2015">第84頁</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>作者提供了洞窟位置、建築形制方面的詳細描述，提及後壁打磨方塊，并迻録宋代願文。</p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <figure rend="center" n="figure" xml:id="WFY_65_2007_w65-0.jpg">
                        <head xml:lang="zh">
                            <hi rend="bold">65</hi>號窟。2007年拍攝</head>
                        <head>Cave <hi rend="bold">65</hi>; photograph taken in 2007</head>
                        <graphic url="WFY_65_2007_w65-0.jpg"/>
                    </figure>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="cave" xml:lang="en">
                <head type="cave">Cave <hi rend="bold">65</hi>
                </head>
                <div>
                    <head>Description</head>
                    <div>
                        <head>Overview</head>
                        <p>This standard cave has straight walls, but was not yet polished and no sutra text was engraved (fig. <ptr target="WFY_65_2007_w65-0.jpg"/>). Its interest is, however, a cyclically dated Song dynasty colophon, corresponding to either February 7, 1007, or February 3, 1067. It mentions Abbot Huiwen. For the text, its translation and the discussion about the date see Introduction, p. <ptr type="infra" target="colophon_Huiwen"/>.<!--It reads: The renunciant Huiwen, who explains [Buddhist] sutras and treatises, setting his mind [on <hi rend="italic">bodhi</hi>], decorated extensively one niche with three figures protecting the land and the Dharma <foreign xml:lang="zh">齊靈濟</foreign>, to be worshipped in eternity. He sincerely askes that the monks of the entire cloister may explain the Way and cultivate their practice. Recorded reverently on the seventeenth day of the first month of a <hi rend="italic">dingwei</hi> year of the august Song [dynasty].
                            <foreign xml:lang="zh">講經論沙門惠文發心，畫廣齊靈濟護法土地三身同一堂，永為供養，意乞闔院僧童，講道修行。以皇宋丁未歲正月十七日了謹記。</foreign>-->
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Location</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>Southern slope, Section D, ca. 280 cm above the walkway. 
                            East of the standing Buddha figure <hi rend="bold">64</hi>, west of cave <hi rend="bold">70</hi>. Above is niche <hi rend="bold">68</hi>.</item>
                            <item>Direction of wall f: 352°.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Shape</head>
                        <p>Simple, regular box shape, without reveal. All three walls have been not yet smoothed, except for three rectangular polished fields from the Song dynasty, once filled with painted figures (fig. <ptr target="WFY_65e_DSC8669_2015.jpg"/>).<note>For the discussion about the painted figures see p. <ptr type="infra" target="colophon_Huiwen"/>.</note> The middle field begins 81 cm above the floor. The polished area is 76 x 65–66 cm. The field to the west begins 78 cm above the floor; its polished area is 69 x 65 cm. The field to the east begins 73 cm above the floor; its polished area is 49 x 55 cm. Above the center of the middle field, a small rectangular protrusion, 29 x 17–18.5 cm, carries the Song dynasty colophon (fig. <ptr target="WFY_65e_colophon_DSC8697.jpg"/>).</p>
                    </div><!--<div>
                        <head>Changes</head>
                        <p>Two rectangular insets have been cut near the entrance, open toward the front, 42 x 64 cm, depth 9 cm (west), 42 x 47, depth 3 cm (east). In the center of the cave are three round insets, diameter 26–28 cm, depth 12 cm (west), diameter 32 cm, depth 10 cm (center), diameter 30–31 cm, depth 12–16 cm (east). </p>
                        <p>Rectangular insets, 20x43, cm depth 4 cm (west) 19x32 cm, depth 8 cm (east).</p>
                        <p>Wall d: 100 cm from the entrance is a triangular incision, 122–134 cm above floor, width 6.5 cm depth 7.5 cm </p>
                        <p>Wall f: 102 cm from the entrance 130–140 cm above the floor, width 7.5 cm depth 7.5 cm </p>
                        <p>Wall c: three fields above the floor. The middle field begins 81 cm above the floor, has above a ca. 2.5 cm wide frame with triangular section. The polished area is 76 x 65–66 cm. The field to the west 78 cm above the floor, polished area is 69 x 65 cm. A rectangular field with engraved characters, 29 x 17–18.5 cm, protrudes above the center of the middle field. The text from the Song time records the name of the monastery.  </p>
                        <p>The cave is unique.</p>
                        <ab>
                            <abbr>LL</abbr>
                        </ab>
                        
                    </div>-->
                    <div>
                        <head>Measurements</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>Wall d: height at the front 236 cm, at the rear 224 cm; width: 190 cm.</item>
                            <item>Wall e: height at midpoint 240 cm; width: 216 cm.</item>
                            <item>Wall f: height at the front 227 cm, at the rear 230 cm; width: 204 cm.</item>
                            <item>Width of entrance opening 192 cm.</item>
                        </list><!-- <list>
                            <head>Diagonals</head>
                            <item>Left front to right rear: 293 cm</item>
                            <item>Right front to left rear 270 cm</item>
                        </list>-->
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Db_Cave65_discussion_en">
                    <head>Discussion</head>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="Dengzhijin1993">37; 40, note 3</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>Deng Zhijin gives a transcription of the colophon by Huiwen, and provides measurements for the field of script where this colophon is located. In his footnote he mentions that Huiwen was, at one time, Head Monk of the Grove of the Reclining Buddha, and he identifies the <hi rend="italic">dingwei </hi>
                                <foreign xml:lang="zh">丁未</foreign> year mentioned in the colophon as 1067.</p>
                            <p/>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="Qin_Zhang_Lei2015">84</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>The authors give a detailed description of the location and architecture of the cave, mentioning the polished areas on the rear wall. They also provide a transcription of the votive inscription from the Song dynasty. </p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <figure rend="center" n="figure" xml:id="WFY_65e_DSC8669_2015.jpg">
                        <head xml:lang="zh">
                            <hi rend="bold">65</hi>號窟正壁。2015年拍攝</head>
                        <head>Rear wall of cave <hi rend="bold">65</hi>; photograph taken in 2015</head>
                        <graphic url="WFY_65e_DSC8669_2015.jpg"/>
                    </figure>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
